<P>
SHERMAN ON THE SIOUX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * While Americans recoil with indignant shock at the holocausts occurring in 
Bosnia and Rwanda, we might be reminded of the advice William Tecumseh Sherman 
gave to President Ulysses S. Grant: "First clear off the buffalo, then clear 
off the Indian. We must act with vindictive earnestness against the Sioux even 
to their total extermination -- men, women and children." 
</P>
<P>
 Our own hands aren't clean. 
