</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sylmar High defensive back Dwight Patton signed a letter of intent to play 
football at Utah State, Sylmar Coach Jeff Engilman said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Patton, a 5-foot-11, 175-pound All-East Valley League selection, took a 
recruiting trip to Utah State last weekend, one week after receiving a score on 
the Scholastic Aptitude Test that met NCAA requirements.It was the only 
recruiting trip taken by Patton. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a big load off his mind," Engilman said. "He's been rejuvenated." 
</P>
<P>
 Patton, who was also the Spartans' leading receiver with 24 catches for 468 
yards and five touchdowns, is the third Sylmar player from the 1993 team to 
earn a scholarship. Running back Tyrone Crenshaw signed with Michigan State and 
defensive back Robert Camacho will play for Cal Poly San Luis Obispo. PAIGE A. 
