<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: LUNKER BASS AT CASITAS THE RULE, NOT EXCEPTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Given the size of the bass coming out of Lake Casitas in recent weeks, it's 
not surprising that a recent tournament at the Ventura County reservoir 
produced outstanding results. 
</P>
<P>
 The first-place team of Dana Rosen and Darin Tochihara set a record for any 
major bass tournament with a six-fish limit totaling 63.26 pounds.  
</P>
<P>
 The catch last Saturday included three fish weighing more than 10 pounds, 
including a 13.52-pounder. 
</P>
<P>
 The biggest bass of the tournament, however, was a 15.47-pounder caught by 
Brian Mitchell of Ventura. Mitchell and Todd Holder of Ojai finished second 
with six fish totaling 36.97 pounds. 
</P>
