<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jason Hodges 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Baseball / Designated Hitter 
</P>
<P>
 Hodges, from Esperanza High, has had several key hits for Cypress this season 
but none bigger than his home run against Riverside April 26.The teams started 
the day tied for first and Riverside had rallied for three runs in the top of 
the sixth to tie it, 3-3. But Hodges led off bottom of the seventh with a home 
run, his second of the game, and Cypress went on to a 4-3 victory. He finished 
the three-game week going six for 11 with three home runs, five runs scored and 
four RBIs. Hodges starts this week hitting .368 with 10 home runs, and he has 
scored 39 runs and driven in 37. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Chris Beck, Orange Coast, shot 75-71 for a 146 to win the Orange Empire 
Conference golf championship. 
</P>
