<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACT LINKS SAN FRANCISCO, HO CHI MINH CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Francisco officials signed a friendship agreement with Ho Chi Minh City, 
becoming the first U.S. city to arrange such a pact since President Clinton 
lifted the trade embargo against Vietnam. 
</P>
<P>
 The agreement calls for a "new era of cooperation and friendship," detailing 
several areas where the cities will work together to establish cultural and 
business relationships, including transportation, art, literature and medicine. 
</P>
<P>
 "More important than the exact details is the spirit of cooperation that this 
represents," said Mayor Frank Jordan, who signed the agreement Monday and 
presented a 12-member Vietnamese delegation with a vintage trolley car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
