<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: ACTIVITIES PLANNED FOR CINCO DE MAYO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Several events are planned in the San Fernando Valley to celebrate Cinco de 
Mayo, commemorating the Battle of Puebla in which ragtag Mexican warriors 
defeated the French army May 5, 1862. Among the offerings: 
</P>
<P>
 Montezuma visit: A celebration with Montezuma, the last Aztec emperor of 
Mexico (portrayed by Fabian Gregory Cordova), will be held from 9 a.m. to 12:30 
p.m. today and Thursday at the outdoor Plaza of Mexican Heritage at Forest Lawn 
Memorial-Park, 6300 Forest Lawn Drive, Hollywood Hills.Performances every 
half-hour. Free. Reservations: (800) 204-3131, Ext. 4743. 
</P>
<P>
 Luncheon for senior citizens: The San Fernando Valley Interfaith Council 
nutrition program will hold a luncheon at 11 a.m. Thursday at these locations: 
Casa Panorama, 14550 Osborne St., Panorama City, information (818) 892-5570; 
Pacoima Senior Center, 11242 Glenoaks Blvd., information (818) 896-7448; 
Trinity Presbyterian Church, 11960 Victory Blvd., North Hollywood, information 
(818) 980-9032, and Las Palmas Park, 505 S. Huntington St., San Fernando, 
information (818) 898-1296. A donation of $1.25 is asked per person. 
</P>
<P>
 Celebration: Mission College will hold a program at noon Thursday in Campus 
Center Room 1 with speakers, food, music by students and dances by children. 
The college is at 13356 Eldridge Ave., Sylmar. Free. Information: (818) 
364-7766. 
</P>
<P>
 Evening event: A Cinco de Mayo celebration with music and dancers will be held 
at 6:30 p.m. Friday at Valley College's Monarch Hall, 5800 Fulton Ave., Van 
Nuys. Free. Information: (818) 781-1200. 
</P>
<P>
 San Fernando Mall: A sidewalk sale for Cinco de Mayo and Mother's Day will be 
held along San Fernando Road between San Fernando Mission Boulevard and 
Chatsworth Street from 11 a.m. to 5 p.m. Saturday. Activities include food, 
entertainment, petting zoo and prizes. The event is sponsored by the San 
Fernando Downtown Mall Assn. Information: (818) 361-1184. 
