GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: GLENDALE; TESTS ORDERED FOR BOY WHO KILLED FRIEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 15-year-old boy who shot and killed a 9-year-old friend in a Glendale 
apartment last year has been ordered to undergo 90 days of psychological and 
psychiatric evaluation. 
</P>
<P>
 The order was given in Pasadena Juvenile Court on Tuesday, about a month after 
the teen-ager was found guilty of second-degree murder. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager, whose identity is being withheld because of his age, is 
expected to return to court for sentencing Aug. 2, said Deputy Dist. Atty. 
Laura Foland-Priver. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager and the victim, Sang Lee, lived in the same apartment complex in 
the 1200 block of Virginia Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager told police that he invited Lee to his apartment to watch 
television Aug. 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Soon after they finished, the older boy went to a living room cabinet and 
pulled out his father's .38-caliber revolver from a shoe box. 
</P>
<P>
 The teen-ager, who was then 14, loaded the gun with one bullet and pulled the 
trigger twice -- hitting Lee in the chest. VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
