<TEXT>
<P>
 A Canyon Country man was killed and two other motorists were injured Tuesday 
morning in a three-vehicle crash on Pearblossom Highway, just east of the 
Antelope Valley Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 Glen W. Harvey, 34, was pronounced dead at the scene of the accident, which 
occurred at 6:30 a.m., California Highway Patrol Officer Tom Hastain said. 
</P>
<P>
 Harvey and Steven Purana, 20, of Llano were driving east on Pearblossom when 
Purana's pickup abruptly changed lanes and struck the rear of Harvey's Honda 
Civic, causing that car to spin out of control. 
