<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; MAN SKATING ACROSS STREET STRUCK BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who was skating across Newhope Street was killed Monday night when he 
was struck by a car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, Julian Mar Cervantes, 21, was skating in a crosswalk at the 
intersection of Newhope and McFadden Avenue, a block from his home, when the 
accident occurred just after 8 p.m., said Lt. Robert Helton. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, an 18-year-old Fountain Valley man, continued northbound on 
Newhope after the collision and crashed into a telephone pole. He suffered 
minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 "The driver was in the left lane, then changed lanes when the traffic in front 
of him stopped, and that's when he struck the pedestrian who was in the 
crosswalk," Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the car was not cited at the scene but the accident remains 
under investigation to determine whether criminal charges should be filed. 
</P>
