<TEXT>
<P>
 Four people were injured Tuesday in a five-car pileup on the northbound Santa 
Ana Freeway near Jamboree Road, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 At 3:15 p.m., traffic slowed suddenly, and a 1977 Chevrolet pickup truck 
driven by a 40-year-old San Fernando woman hit the vehicle in front, causing a 
chain reaction of crashes, the CHP said. 
</P>
<P>
 Four people were taken to hospitals with minor to major injuries. Several had 
to be freed with machinery. None of the drivers was cited by officers. 
</P>
<P>
 The collision caused a 45-minute SigAlert in the northbound lanes. 
