<P>
WEBBER CHOSEN ROOKIE OF YEAR OVER HARDAWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Webber, who helped make the Golden State Warriors the NBA's most 
improved team, Tuesday was chosen as the league's rookie of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 The first of Michigan's Fab Five to play in the NBA and the youngest player in 
the league, Webber edged Orlando's Anfernee Hardaway, the player Golden State 
drafted third and sent to the Magic for the rights to Webber, the No. 1 
selection last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Webber received 53 votes to 47 for Hardaway in balloting by a panel of sports 
writers and broadcasters. Webber averaged 17.5 points, 9.1 rebounds, 3.6 
assists, 2.2 blocks and 1.2 steals. 
</P>
