<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fox Signs Top Independent Animation Producers: Don Bluth and Gary Goldman, the 
team responsible for animated films such as "The Land Before Time," "An 
American Tail" and "Hans Christian Andersen's Thumbelina," signed a long-term 
deal to produce animated features for 20th Century Fox's new family films 
division. Fox is committing more than $100 million to the animation company, 
scheduled for its first film release in late 1996. Bluth will begin working at 
Fox at the end of this month, Goldman in July. 
</P>
