<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Film Studio Planned in Baja: Vancouver, British Columbia-based Beacon Studios 
said it will develop a 150-acre film studio complex in Bajamar, Mexico, near 
Ensenada.The Canadian film investment organization said it spent $29 million to 
acquire the site, where it plans to build six sound stages for use in making 
motion pictures, television shows and commercials. Construction is to begin 
next year. The company said the project was inspired by the North American Free 
Trade Agreement. 
</P>
