<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: CUE NETWORK OKS JOINT VENTURE IN SOUTHEAST ASIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CUE Network Corp. said it has agreed to form a joint venture company to 
provide international paging and global positioning services in Singapore and 
throughout Southeast Asia. 
</P>
<P>
 Other countries to be served by the new company, CUE Southeast Asia 
Partnership Ltd., include Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, the Philippines and 
Vietnam. 
</P>
<P>
 CUE's partner, a unit of a the Singapore trade union group National Trades 
Union Congress, operates that nation's first private radio station. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine-based CUE provides nationwide and regional messaging services 
throughout North America through the facilities of over 360 FM radio stations. 
The Singapore group, NTUC Voice Cooperative, broadcasts over two FM frequencies 
there. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to its paging network, CUE markets equipment that increases the 
accuracy of commercially available global positioning services. 
</P>
<P>
 Global positioning is a navigation tool using Department of Defense Global 
Positioning Satellites to establish the user's location: CUE says commercial 
position finding systems are accurate to within about 100 yards and that its 
system increases accuracy to within five yards. So-called GPS systems have many 
users including trucking and shipping fleet operators, ambulance companies, 
police and fire departments, surveyors, and map makers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
